## Section 2 — Navigation Architecture: Pill Toggle

### 2.1 Toggle Placement and Structure

The pill toggle sits at the top of the Scenario Planner tab content area, directly below the page header. It is always visible regardless of which mode is active. It is not a full tab bar — it is a lightweight mode switcher.

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  Scenario Planner                                   │
│  Advanced growth modeling and scenario comparison   │
│                                                     │
│        [ Build Scenario ]  [ Compare ]              │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

**Visual spec:**
- Pill container: rounded rectangle, light gray background or subtle border
- Active mode: filled pill segment, dark background, white text
- Inactive mode: transparent, medium-weight text, hover state darkens slightly
- Width: auto-sized to label length, not full-width
- Centered or left-aligned below the page header — consistent with platform conventions
- No icons required — labels are self-explanatory

**Toggle state is managed as:** `mode: 'build' | 'compare'`

Default on page load: `'build'`

Exception: if the founder arrives via "View in Comparison" CTA from the post-save confirmation, `mode` initializes as `'compare'`.

### 2.2 Toggle Behavior

Switching modes is instant — no loading state, no animation delay. The content below the toggle swaps completely. Build mode content and Compare mode content do not coexist on the same scroll — one replaces the other.

No confirmation required to switch modes. Any unsaved in-progress scenario in Build mode is preserved in local state — switching to Compare and back does not reset the Build form.

### 2.3 Compare Mode Entry — No Scenario Required

Compare mode is always accessible regardless of whether a scenario was just created. A founder can land on the Scenario Planner page and click directly into Compare. The Compare mode handles its own empty state if no scenarios exist in their library.

