### 3.2 Section A — Scenario Selector

**Purpose:** Let the founder select which saved scenarios to bring into the active comparison. Handles large scenario libraries gracefully via dropdown rather than card grid.

#### Empty State (No Scenarios Selected)

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  Select scenarios to compare                        │
│                                                     │
│  [ + Add Scenario ▾ ]                               │
│                                                     │
│  Select up to 3 scenarios. Your current agency      │
│  baseline is always included as the reference.      │
│                                                     │
│  No scenarios yet?                                  │
│  → Build your first scenario in the Build tab       │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

#### Add Scenario Dropdown

Clicking "Add Scenario" opens a searchable dropdown list of all the founder's saved scenarios. Each item in the list shows:

```
[ Scenario Name ]          GVI: 67  ·  Healthy Velocity  ·  24mo
[ Active Growth — 24mo ]   GVI: 67  ·  Healthy Velocity  ·  24mo
[ Steady Climb — 18mo  ]   GVI: 74  ·  Healthy Velocity  ·  18mo
[ Rocket Ship — 24mo   ]   GVI: 44  ·  Active Pressure   ·  24mo
```

- Scenarios already selected in the active comparison are shown with a checkmark and are not re-selectable
- Dropdown is searchable — text input at top filters the list
- Maximum 3 selections enforced — once 3 are selected the dropdown disables with a tooltip: "Maximum 3 scenarios. Remove one to add another."

#### Active Selection State

Once scenarios are selected, the selector section shows a compact row of selected scenario chips with an "Add" button if slots remain:

```
[ ✕ Active Growth — 24mo ]  [ ✕ Steady Climb — 18mo ]  [ ✕ Rocket Ship — 24mo ]  [ All 3 selected ]
```

- Each chip has an ✕ to remove it from the comparison
- Removing a scenario immediately updates all downstream sections

